1) Usually while starting the spring Application for the first time after configuration, 
you may end up getting the following error :

ERROR : 
springboot java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Sources must not be empty.

Resolution : 
* Check your eclipse debug configurations and make sure your Main class is not set to the followng :
org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication 

If yes, change the entry to your fully qualified main class Name


2) Starting a mySql server fails with error :
ERROR 2002 (HY000): Can't connect to local MySQL server through socket '/tmp/mysql.sock' (2)

Resolution :
i) On a mac or linux 
  find . -name mysql // to find the installation path for mysql
  //go to the installation directory path from above and type
  mysql.server start

